# Test data only

Never use real client names, project names, or personal/business email addresses in tests, fixtures, README examples, or config samples.

## Use

- Projects: `Acme`, `Gamma`, `Demo` (fictional names)
- Mailboxes: `alice@example.com`, `alice@gmail.com`
- Contacts: `Bob Client <bob@client.example.com>`, `Carol Contact <carol@client.example.com>`
- Subjects: `acme - docs`, `Quarterly Report`, `Product feedback survey`
- Shared constants: `tests/sample_data.py` (`MAILBOX`, `CLIENT_HEADER`, `PROJECT_ACME`, etc.)
- Paths: `~/Documents/Obsidian Vault` or `/path/to/vault` — not real home directories

## Do not use

- Real client, employer, or vault project names
- Real domains or contact emails from production mail or your Obsidian vault
- Real thread content copied from production emails

## When adding tests

1. Import or mirror names from `tests/sample_data.py` when practical.
2. Review the diff for anything that looks like a real person, company, or project before committing.
3. `pyproject.toml` author metadata is fine; test bodies and fixtures are not.
